Use these three startup sequences.

1. Minimal local dev
```powershell
mvn clean package
docker compose up --build
```

2. Full stack with observability
```powershell
mvn clean package
docker compose --profile observability up --build
```

3. Full stack with observability + Ollama
```powershell
mvn clean package
docker compose --profile observability --profile ai up --build
```

Order matters:
- build the JAR first
- then start Compose
- then add the profiles you want

If you want, I can also give you the exact shutdown commands for each case.

Shutdown commands for the same three cases:

1. Minimal local dev
```powershell
docker compose down
```

2. Full stack with observability
```powershell
docker compose --profile observability down
```

3. Full stack with observability + Ollama
```powershell
docker compose --profile observability --profile ai down
```

If you also want to wipe the persistent data volumes for a clean reset:
```powershell
docker compose down -v
```

